We recommended that the Local Chief Executive:
a. Ensure that the 20% Development Fund of the Municipality be utilized only to fund priority programs or projects included in the approved Annual Investment Plan (AIP) which partake the nature of investment or capital expenditures in compliance and in accordance with the provisions DBM-DOF- DILG JMC No. 1 dated November 4, 2020 and of DILG-DBM Joint Memorandum Circular No. 2017-1 to ensure its optimal utilization;
b. Require the MPDC to regularly monitor the 20% development projects to ensure the efficient and effective implementation thereof; and submit accomplishment report to the Audit Team;
c. Direct the BAC-Secretariat to submit the documents relative to the conduct of contract review and the Municipal Engineer to prepare letter request for technical inspection of the said projects; and
d. Augment additional staff in the BAC-Secretariat to assist in the compilation, segregation and preparation of all supporting documents due for submission to the Audit Team.

We recommended to the Local Chief Executive the following:
a. Enjoin the submission of lacking documents, such as certification from the head of the health facility of the number of hours rendered by each Health Care Worker (HCW) duly supported with Daily Time Records in compliance with the provisions of DBM and DOH Joint Circular No. 2022-001 dated February 10, 2022;
b. Required the Heads of the LGU’s health facilities to require each HCW to sign a quitclaim with an undertaking that in case the HCWs receive OCA benefits twice or more from one (1) or more health facilities, the HCWs shall return the excess amount; and;
c. Direct the Accountant to require HCWs and all the casual and contractual employees to prepare and submit Accomplishment Report signed by the immediate supervisors before processing claims for payment in compliance with COA Circular No. 2012-001;

We recommended to the Local Chief Executive the following:
a. Strictly comply with the rules and regulations under COA Circular No. 2023-004 dated June 14, 2023, prescribing the Updated Documentary Requirement for Common Government Transactions;
b. Require the Municipal Accountant to scrutinize the completeness of transactions, disbursement vouchers be supported with complete documentation before payment shall be made;
c. Direct the OIC-Municipal Engineer to coordinate with the Accounting Office and submit the required supporting documents that emanate from his office; and
d. Instruct the BAC and BAC-Secretariat to strictly comply with the requirements under COA Circular No. 2009-001 dated February 12, 2009 on the submission of contracts.

